'Memory leak\', \'Compile error\', \'Race condition\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'NullSafety\', \'Errors\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>String text = \"\";\\nwhile ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\\n  text = text + line;\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>StringBuilder sb = new StringBuilder();\\nwhile ((line = reader.readLine()) != null) {\\n  sb.append(line);\\n}\\nString text = sb.toString();\\n</code></pre>Which principle does the good code demonstrate?\', options=[\'Testability\', \'Performance and efficiency\', \'Security\', \'Abstraction\'], correct_options=[1], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'Performance\', \'BadCode\'], source=\'http://varianceexplained.org/programming/bad-code/\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>List<String> filterLarge(List<String> items) {\\n  for (int i = 0; i < items.size(); i++) {\\n    if (items.get(i).length() <= 3) {\\n      items.remove(i);\\n      i--;\\n    }\\n  }\\n  return items;\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>List<String> filterLarge(List<String> items) {\\n  return items.stream()\\n      .filter(s -> s.length() > 3)\\n      .collect(Collectors.toList());\\n}\\n</code></pre>What unexpected behavior might the bad code produce?\', options=[\'Concurrent modification exception\', \'NullPointerException\', \'Index skipping and incorrect filtering\', \'Memory leak\'], correct_options=[2], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'SideEffects\', \'Streams\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>int sqrt(int x) {\\n  return (int)Math.sqrt(x);\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>int sqrt(int x) {\\n  if (x < 0) throw new IllegalArgumentException(\"x must be non-negative\");\\n  return (int)Math.sqrt(x);\\n}\\n</code></pre>What benefit does adding the check provide?\', options=[\'Prevention of invalid input misuse\', \'Better performance\', \'Longer code\', \'Hides implementation\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'DefensiveCoding\', \'Contracts\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>class UserService {\\n  void register(User u) {\\n    Connection c = DriverManager.getConnection(...);\\n    // business logic\\n    // logging to file\\n    c.close();\\n  }\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>class UserService {\\n  private final UserRepository repo;\\n  private final Logger logger;\\n  UserService(UserRepository repo, Logger logger) { ... }\\n  void register(User u) {\\n    repo.save(u);\\n    logger.info(\"User saved\");\\n  }\\n}\\n</code></pre>Which cohesion type does the good design demonstrate?\', options=[\'Functional cohesion\', \'Sequential cohesion\', \'Coincidental cohesion\', \'Temporal cohesion\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'Cohesion\', \'Classes\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>if (s == String.Empty) { ... }</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>if (s == \"\") { ... }</code></pre>According to Wil Shipley, why is the good code considered better?\', options=[\'Reduced verbosity improves readability\', \'Compiler optimization\', \'Semantic clarity\', \'Security\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'Brevity\', \'Readability\'], source=\'https://blog.codinghorror.com/the-best-code-is-no-code-at-all/\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>boolean isStockAvailable(String item) {\\n  Database db = new Database();\\n  int count = db.queryStock(item);\\n  return count > 0;\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>class StockService {\\n  private final StockRepository repo;\\n  boolean isStockAvailable(String item) {\\n    int count = repo.getStock(item);\\n    return count > 0;\\n  }\\n}\\n</code></pre>Why is the latter more testable?\', options=[\'Can mock repository\', \'Improves performance\', \'Decreases code size\', \'Harder to modify\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'Testability\', \'DI\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code duplicates paragraph-splitting logic in two places:  \\n<pre><code>List<String> splitParaA(String text) { ... }\\nList<String> splitParaB(String text) { ... same logic ... }\\n</code></pre>Good code extracts a single ParagraphFinder class and reuses it. Which benefit does this achieve?\', options=[\'Reduced duplication\', \'Tighter coupling\', \'Increased file count\', \'Harder to test\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'DRY\', \'Reusability\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><code>HttpConnection connect(String url) {\\n  // open socket, write HTTP, parse headers\\n}\\n</code></pre>Good code:  \\n<pre><code>HttpConnection connection = HttpConnection.connect(\"http://example.com\");\\n</code></pre>What is the main advantage of the good code?\', options=[\'Layers of abstraction hide complexity\', \'Lower performance\', \'Harder to debug\', \'Increased dependencies\'], correct_options=[0], difficulty_level=\'Medium\', tags=[\'Abstraction\', \'Readability\'], source=\'Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf\', type=\'multiple_choice\'), _Question(question=\'Bad code:  \\n<pre><co