INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('26a621a5-fd35-4610-9c21-0b13b8390c3f','user-admin-001','686a9350-c95b-4ab5-9e08-af1d8a335b63','53fa3c1d-50e6-4c78-b322-6488865517d0','Consider the following Python functions:\n<pre><code>\ndef tail_fact(n, acc=1):\n    if n == 0:\n        return acc\n    else:\n        return tail_fact(n-1, acc * n)\ndef nontail_fact(n):\n    if n == 1:\n        return 1\n    else:\n        return n * nontail_fact(n-1)\n</code></pre>\nWhich statement accurately describes their recursion patterns and the potential for optimization?','[\"tail_fact is tail-recursive and can be optimized into an iteration by languages that support tail-call elimination; nontail_fact is non-tail recursive and cannot be optimized this way.\", \"tail_fact is non-tail recursive because the multiplication happens before its recursive call; nontail_fact is tail-recursive since multiplication happens after the call.\", \"Both functions are tail-recursive and would be optimized identically by Python’s interpreter.\", \"Neither function is recursive; both use loops internally.\"]','[0]','easy','[\"tail recursion\", \"non-tail recursion\"]','https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python/recursion-in-python/',0,0,'2025-10-06 17:36:54','2025-10-06 17:36:54','mcq');
