INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('428ddaeb-fe5b-410f-b32c-d5fa4b829709','user-admin-001','686a9350-c95b-4ab5-9e08-af1d8a335b63','53fa3c1d-50e6-4c78-b322-6488865517d0','Consider the following tail-recursive factorial function with an accumulator:\n\n<pre><code>\ndef tail_fact(n, acc=1):\n    if n == 0:\n        return acc\n    else:\n        return tail_fact(n-1, acc * n)\n</code></pre>\n\nWhich feature of this implementation makes it a tail-recursive function?','[\"The recursive call is the last operation, with all multiplication done by passing the updated accumulator\", \"The multiplication occurs after the recursive call returns, ensuring the result is built afterward\", \"It uses a default accumulator parameter set to 1\", \"It uses a base case checking n == 0 to stop recursion\"]','[0]','easy','[\"tail recursion\", \"factorial\"]','https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python/recursion-in-python/',0,0,'2025-10-06 17:36:54','2025-10-06 17:36:54','mcq');
