INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('55f73bd1-05b3-43ea-b0ad-c4f626ac3193','user-admin-001','87587b16-87be-44d5-b88e-8f0fb54f586b','6c68a915-6bd2-4a98-a9f0-6f76e55889d1','Consider the following code snippet:\n\n<pre><code>\n// Python-like\n def compute_tax(amount):\n     return amount * 0.2\n\n def final_price(base_price):\n     return base_price + compute_tax(base_price)\n\n def discounted_price(base_price, discount_rate):\n     discounted = base_price * discount_rate\n     return base_price - discounted + compute_tax(base_price - discounted)\n</code></pre>\n\nTrue or False: Centralizing the tax calculation in the pure function `compute_tax` demonstrates the DRY principle and enhances the code’s reusability and maintainability by avoiding repeated tax logic.','[\"True\", \"False\"]','[0]','medium','[\"DRY\", \"PureFunctions\"]','https://medium.com/geekculture/what-is-a-good-code-and-why-is-it-all-about-others-not-ourselves-40730c7a03e5',0,0,'2025-10-08 11:22:09','2025-10-08 11:22:09','true_false');
