INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('5e707cb3-808d-4127-ae10-42cfb611ec90','user-admin-001','1f9f921d-8a65-4a6e-9b74-96a6979da10b','8cceadf0-de0e-430d-a195-50d9d961ce79','Consider the following pseudo-code that renders 10,000 graphic objects by sharing one of 10 intrinsic shape instances and supplying extrinsic transform data per draw call:\n<pre><code>// Creating graphic objects\nfor i in range(10000):\n    shape = factory.getShape(\"type\" + str(i % 10))\n    shape.draw(x[i], y[i])\n</code></pre>\nEach intrinsic shape instance occupies ~2 MB, and each extrinsic transform (position/rotation) is ~1 KB per object. Calculate the approximate total memory usage using the Flyweight pattern versus a naive implementation that allocates both intrinsic and extrinsic data per object, and determine the percentage of memory saved by Flyweight.','[\"Flyweight uses ~30 MB total vs ~20,010 MB naive, saving ~99.85%\", \"Flyweight uses ~2,010 MB total vs ~20,010 MB naive, saving ~90%\", \"Flyweight uses ~20,010 MB total vs ~20,010 MB naive, saving 0%\", \"Flyweight uses ~200 MB total vs ~20,010 MB naive, saving ~99%\"]','[0]','hard','[\"Flyweight\", \"Memory Optimization\"]','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_design_pattern',0,0,'2025-10-08 21:53:59','2025-10-08 21:53:59','mcq');
