INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('68718a83-0ca1-4d3d-a547-ecb59bb164c1','101','80e9258e-0884-4728-97eb-b5381527a0a7','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','Examine these two HTML approaches for styling a warning message:\n\nSnippet A:\n<pre><code><p style=\"color: red; font-size: 16px;\">Warning message</p>\n</code></pre>\n\nSnippet B:\n<pre><code>/* In CSS file */\n.error { color: red; font-size: 16px; }\n\n<!-- In HTML -->\n<p class=\"error\">Warning message</p>\n</code></pre>\n\nWhich snippet represents better maintainability practices?','[\"Snippet A; it keeps style close to content.\", \"Snippet B; it separates style into CSS classes.\", \"Snippet A; inline CSS is faster to render.\", \"Snippet B; it duplicates styling rules.\"]','[1]','Medium','[\"Maintainability\", \"CSS\"]','https://www.dbswebsite.com/blog/the-case-against-bad-code/',1,0,'2025-09-15 20:33:44','2025-09-15 20:33:44','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('68e381ea-1580-4e7a-93e7-ed4ecece6af6','101','1ae3f056-2a49-4bff-9c8c-5fe084e2d83b','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','A function returns a tuple of (latitude, longitude). Which approach makes the code easier to use and less error-prone?\n\nBad code:\n<pre><code>def get_coordinates():\n    # returns latitude, longitude\n    return 51.5074, -0.1278\n\nlat, lon = get_coordinates()\n</code></pre>\nGood code:\n<pre><code>from collections import namedtuple\n\nCoordinates = namedtuple(\'Coordinates\', [\'latitude\', \'longitude\'])\n\ndef get_coordinates():\n    return Coordinates(latitude=51.5074, longitude=-0.1278)\n\ncoords = get_coordinates()\nlat = coords.latitude\nlon = coords.longitude\n</code></pre>\n','[\"Tuple version is safer\", \"Namedtuple version is safer\", \"Both are equally clear\", \"Neither is recommended\"]','[1]','Medium','[\"Data Types\", \"Readability\"]','Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- Anna’s Archive.pdf (chapter 7.3)“Avoid overly general data types”',0,0,'2025-09-16 11:20:01','2025-09-16 11:20:01','mcq');
