INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('b9700544-a367-46e9-935b-de767238391d','101','default','23d58d77-91d2-49a0-83ea-dde75a5d6df8','In the following Python-like snippet, a developer uses both an assert statement and a pytest unit test to enforce the invariant that a count must be non-negative:\n\n<pre><code>\n// Python\n def set_count(n):\n     assert n >= 0, \"Count must be non-negative\"\n     return n\n\ndef test_set_count_raises():\n    with pytest.raises(AssertionError):\n        set_count(-1)\n</code></pre>\n\nWhich of the following best describes the primary benefit of adding the automated test alongside the in-code assertion?','[\"It verifies that the in-code assertion triggers correctly for invalid inputs and ensures future changes don’t regress this behavior in an automated CI pipeline.\", \"It eliminates the need for the in-code assertion in production, since the unit test will catch any invalid calls at runtime.\", \"It confirms that the function returns an integer for all valid inputs, covering type consistency.\", \"It guarantees that the assertion remains enabled even when Python runs in optimized (-O) mode.\"]','[0]','medium','[\"code assertions\", \"automated testing\"]','https://mitcommlab.mit.edu/broad/commkit/coding-mindset/',0,0,'2025-10-06 09:54:39','2025-10-06 09:54:39','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('bb25d45e-c715-4260-9c88-8ee17e27f1cc','101','fff1e95c-c568-4ea4-9eae-ef9918da7474','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','Which of the following scenarios best illustrates a violation of the DRY (Don\'t Repeat Yourself) principle?','[\"A utility function called by multiple components\", \"Duplicated logic to calculate the same value in two classes\", \"A single method performing one clear task\", \"Well-named, reusable modules\"]','[1]','Medium','[\"DRY\", \"Principle\"]','https://gerlacdt.github.io/blog/posts/clean_code/',0,0,'2025-09-15 09:24:36','2025-09-15 09:24:36','mcq');
