INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('c64588d1-51e7-4cf0-a38e-7f3965fd68a7','user-admin-001','686a9350-c95b-4ab5-9e08-af1d8a335b63','53fa3c1d-50e6-4c78-b322-6488865517d0','Examine the following function definition and call:\n<pre><code>\ndef example(a, b=2, *args, **kwargs):\n    print(a, b, args, kwargs)\n</code></pre>\nWhat is printed when calling example(1, 3, 4, 5, x=6, y=7)?','[\"1 2 (3, 4, 5) {\'x\': 6, \'y\': 7}\", \"1 3 (4, 5) {\'x\': 6, \'y\': 7}\", \"1 3 [4, 5] {\'x\': 6, \'y\': 7}\", \"1 2 [4, 5] {\'x\': 6, \'y\': 7}\"]','[1]','easy','[\"default\", \"args\", \"kwargs\"]','https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/python/python-functions/',0,0,'2025-10-07 15:54:18','2025-10-07 15:54:18','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('c6fa4f18-46e6-4dbb-962a-6742e4662ad1','user-admin-001','1f9f921d-8a65-4a6e-9b74-96a6979da10b','8cceadf0-de0e-430d-a195-50d9d961ce79','Consider the following Python-like pseudocode for a Subject implementing both push and pull notification models:\n\n<pre><code>\nclass Subject:\n    state = {...}\n    observers = []\n    def notify_push(self):\n        for obs in self.observers:\n            obs.update(self.state)\n    def notify_pull(self):\n        for obs in self.observers:\n            obs.update(self)\nclass Observer:\n    def update(self, info):\n        # push: info is full state dict\n        # pull: info is Subject instance\n        pass\n</code></pre>\n\nIn a system where the Subject’s state contains a large set of metrics but each Observer needs only a small subset, and network bandwidth between Subject and Observers is constrained, which notification model is generally more efficient and why?','[\"Push model, because sending the entire state once avoids multiple remote calls and reduces protocol overhead.\", \"Pull model, because Observers retrieve only the specific metrics they need, minimizing data transfer over the network.\", \"Push model, because the Subject can filter and package only the required fields per Observer at the time of notification.\", \"Pull model, because it completely decouples the Subject from Observers’ data requirements, simplifying the design. \"]','[1]','hard','[\"Observer\", \"Notification\"]','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Observer_pattern',0,0,'2025-10-08 21:53:59','2025-10-08 21:53:59','mcq');
