INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('c8d012e3-7c34-4275-8253-7cfefe63db6b','user-admin-001','1f9f921d-8a65-4a6e-9b74-96a6979da10b','8cceadf0-de0e-430d-a195-50d9d961ce79','Consider the following usage snippet of the Command pattern:\n\n<pre><code>\n// Client code\ninvoker.setCommand(new CopyCommand(textEditor))\ninvoker.execute()\n</code></pre>\n\nWhich of the following statements is MOST characteristic of the information you would find in the Consequences section of the GoF documentation for this pattern, as opposed to the Intent section?','[\"Encapsulates a request as an object, thereby letting you parameterize clients with different requests.\", \"Improves flexibility by decoupling sender and receiver, and supports undo/redo via maintaining a history of command objects, at the cost of increasing the number of classes and complexity of object management.\", \"Defines an interface for executing an operation without specifying the concrete class that implements it.\", \"Presents real-world examples of existing systems where this pattern has been successfully applied.\"]','[1]','hard','[\"Intent\", \"Consequences\"]','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_design_pattern',0,0,'2025-10-08 21:53:59','2025-10-08 21:53:59','mcq');
