INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('d09c7bd1-9f9d-4de7-8927-82e19fadf460','101','45f977b0-5088-4fb6-b4f7-a680e167e063','3dce6102-6fb1-4295-9cc1-c5066e8f1844','A developer modifies file1.txt, file2.txt, and file3.txt. They want to include only file1 and file2 in the next snapshot. They run:\n\n<pre><code>\ngit add file1.txt file2.txt\ngit commit -m \"Partial update\"\n</code></pre>\n\nWhich of the following best describes the state of the repository after these commands?','[\"A new commit is created containing changes to file1.txt and file2.txt; file3.txt remains modified in the working directory and uncommitted.\", \"A new commit is created containing changes to all three files; the staging area and working directory are both cleared.\", \"Only file3.txt changes are included in the commit because it was modified last; changes to file1.txt and file2.txt remain staged.\", \"No commit is created because git add must stage all files before commit; the command fails.\"]','[0]','medium','[\"staging\", \"commit\"]','https://docs.github.com/en/get-started/using-git/about-git',0,0,'2025-09-30 23:41:30','2025-09-30 23:41:30','mcq');
