INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('d36875b0-c9bd-49fe-9b99-c183dde36a7b','101','1ae3f056-2a49-4bff-9c8c-5fe084e2d83b','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','Given these two fragments:\nBad code:\n<pre><code>if user.is_active:\n    if user.age >= 18:\n        if user.has_passed_background_check:\n            grant_access()\n</code></pre>\nGood code:\n<pre><code>if not user.is_active:\n    return\nif user.age < 18:\n    return\nif not user.has_passed_background_check:\n    return\ngrant_access()\n</code></pre>\nWhat advantage does the “Good code” approach provide over the “Bad code”?','[\"It avoids guard clauses\", \"It reduces code duplication\", \"It minimizes nesting and improves clarity\", \"It uses more Boolean operations\"]','[2]','Medium','[\"Nesting\", \"Readability\"]','Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- Anna’s Archive.pdf (chapter 5.5)“Avoid deeply nesting code”',0,0,'2025-09-16 11:20:01','2025-09-16 11:20:01','mcq');
