INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('e36639af-78d7-4bd5-8713-52d4e7f80749','user-admin-001','1f9f921d-8a65-4a6e-9b74-96a6979da10b','8cceadf0-de0e-430d-a195-50d9d961ce79','<pre><code>// Java-like Singleton with double-checked locking\nclass Singleton {\n    private static Singleton instance = null;\n    private Singleton() {}\n    public static Singleton getInstance() {\n        if (instance == null) {\n            synchronized(Singleton.class) {\n                if (instance == null) {\n                    instance = new Singleton();\n                }\n            }\n        }\n        return instance;\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\nWhich modification ensures thread safety by preventing instruction reordering and guaranteeing visibility of the instance?','[\"Declare the static instance field as volatile.\", \"Synchronize the entire getInstance() method instead of using double-checked locking.\", \"Switch to the initialization-on-demand holder idiom using a nested static class.\", \"Mark the private constructor as synchronized.\"]','[0]','hard','[\"Singleton\", \"Concurrency\"]','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_design_pattern',0,0,'2025-10-08 21:53:59','2025-10-08 21:53:59','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('e3b9d675-5880-4c3d-b947-4916a1a37158','101','4982c0da-e4ec-4bb3-8724-e84f6e4994f4','23d58d77-91d2-49a0-83ea-dde75a5d6df8','Which coding practice best leverages our visual ability to recognize spatial patterns and order in code?','[\"Using vertical alignment and consistent indentation to group related code blocks\", \"Minimizing all whitespace to fit more code on the screen\", \"Relying solely on comments instead of structural conventions\", \"Packing multiple statements on a single line for brevity\"]','[0]','easy','[\"code style\", \"structure\"]','https://mitcommlab.mit.edu/broad/commkit/coding-mindset/',0,0,'2025-10-01 11:06:01','2025-10-01 11:06:01','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('e465b8a5-88a7-40ab-ac62-21c88ea932ab','user-admin-001','1f9f921d-8a65-4a6e-9b74-96a6979da10b','8cceadf0-de0e-430d-a195-50d9d961ce79','Consider the following pseudocode illustrating two creational patterns:\n<pre><code>\n// Abstract Factory\ninterface UIFactory {\n    createButton();\n    createCheckbox();\n}\n// Factory Method\nabstract class Document {\n    abstract createPage();\n}\n</code></pre>\nWhich statement correctly contrasts the intent and structural consequences of the Factory Method versus the Abstract Factory pattern?','[\"Abstract Factory pattern can be implemented by composing several Factory Method implementations, each responsible for a particular product type, thus offering greater flexibility when introducing new product types at runtime.\", \"Factory Method pattern promotes composition over inheritance by encapsulating object creation in separate factory classes, making it easier to add new products to the system without altering existing code.\", \"Abstract Factory defines interfaces for creating related objects, ensuring that products from the same family are used together, while Factory Method relies on subclassing to decide which concrete product to instantiate, focusing on a single product.\", \"Factory Method is suited for creating families of related products through a unified interface, whereas Abstract Factory is specialized for creating one type of product with various configurations.\"]','[2]','hard','[\"Creational Patterns\", \"Abstract Factory\"]','https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Software_design_pattern',0,0,'2025-10-08 21:53:59','2025-10-08 21:53:59','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('e515e195-7afb-4fd6-b1c3-6a9b03c30494','101','113bba62-604b-430b-a8e5-4605a157a318','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','Bad code:  \n<pre><code>boolean isStockAvailable(String item) {\n  Database db = new Database();\n  int count = db.queryStock(item);\n  return count > 0;\n}\n</code></pre>Good code:  \n<pre><code>class StockService {\n  private final StockRepository repo;\n  boolean isStockAvailable(String item) {\n    int count = repo.getStock(item);\n    return count > 0;\n  }\n}\n</code></pre>Why is the latter more testable?','[\"Can mock repository\", \"Improves performance\", \"Decreases code size\", \"Harder to modify\"]','[0]','Medium','[\"Testability\", \"DI\"]','Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- 1, 2021 -- Manning Publications -- Anna’s Archive.pdf',0,0,'2025-09-16 11:18:25','2025-09-16 11:18:25','mcq');
