INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('fc04d99f-090c-4af3-8808-8a24ae62d832','101','default','23d58d77-91d2-49a0-83ea-dde75a5d6df8','Consider this multi-language snippet:\n<pre><code>\n// Python function\ndef load_data_file(path):\n    ...\n\n// Java class\npublic class UserAccountManager { ... }\n\n// C macro constant\n#define BUFFER_SIZE_LIMIT 1024\n</code></pre>\nWhich naming conventions are being followed for the Python function, the Java class, and the C macro constant, respectively?','[\"snake_case, CamelCase, UPPER_CASE\", \"camelCase, CamelCase, snake_case\", \"PascalCase, UPPER_CASE, lowercase\", \"snake_case, camelCase, UPPER_case\"]','[0]','medium','[\"naming\", \"code style\"]','https://mitcommlab.mit.edu/broad/commkit/coding-and-comment-style/',0,0,'2025-10-06 09:54:39','2025-10-06 09:54:39','mcq');
INSERT INTO `questions` VALUES ('ff7e023a-012b-4859-a741-6218a9da10b7','101','1ae3f056-2a49-4bff-9c8c-5fe084e2d83b','066c011c-a649-4957-a54d-1a7cd2d7d7f4','Which issue arises with the bad version?\nBad code:\n<pre><code>counter = 0\n\ndef increment():\n    global counter\n    counter += 1\n</code></pre>\nGood code:\n<pre><code>def make_counter():\n    count = 0\n    def inc():\n        nonlocal count\n        count += 1\n        return count\n    return inc\n\nincrement = make_counter()\n</code></pre>','[\"Global side effects\", \"Cleaner semantics\", \"Syntax error\", \"Fewer functions\"]','[0]','Medium','[\"Global State\", \"Side Effects\"]','Good Code, Bad Code -- Tom Long -- Anna’s Archive.pdf (chapter 9.2)“Beware of global state”',0,0,'2025-09-16 11:20:01','2025-09-16 11:20:01','mcq');
